# Next.js app router

- **Route groups**: Use route groups for organising routes
- **Layouts**: Use nested layouts for shared UI
- **Loading states**: Implement loading states with Suspense
- **Error boundaries**: Use error boundaries for error handling
- **Metadata**: Use metadata API for SEO optimisation
- **Server actions**: Use server actions for form submissions

## App router patterns

- **Route groups**: Use parentheses for route groups `(app)`, `(auth)`
- **Layouts**: Create nested layouts for shared UI
- **Pages**: Use page.tsx for route pages
- **Loading**: Use loading.tsx for loading states
- **Error**: Use error.tsx for error boundaries
- **Not found**: Use not-found.tsx for 404 pages

## Route structure

```
app/
├── (app)/
│   ├── layout.tsx
│   ├── page.tsx
│   ├── surveys/
│   │   ├── [surveyId]/
│   │   │   ├── layout.tsx
│   │   │   ├── page.tsx
│   │   │   ├── questions/
│   │   │   └── responses/
│   │   ├── create/
│   │   └── page.tsx
│   └── campaigns/
├── (auth)/
│   └── auth/
└── api/
    └── trpc/
```

## Server components

```typescript
// Server component
const SurveyDetailsPage: React.FC<Props> = async ({params}) => {
  const {surveyId} = await params;
  prefetch(trpc.surveys.get.queryOptions(surveyId));

  return (
    <HydrateClient>
      <Container>
        <SurveyOverview surveyId={surveyId} />
      </Container>
    </HydrateClient>
  );
};
```

## Client components

```typescript
'use client';

// Client component
const Form: React.FC = () => {
  const methods = useForm<FormData>({
    resolver: zodResolver(formSchema)
  });

  return (
    <FormProvider {...methods}>
      <form onSubmit={methods.handleSubmit(handleSubmit)}>
        {/* form fields */}
      </form>
    </FormProvider>
  );
};
```

## Loading & error states

- **Loading states**: Use Suspense for loading states
- **Error boundaries**: Implement error boundaries for error handling
- **Skeleton loading**: Use skeleton components for better UX
- **Error recovery**: Provide error recovery options
- **Progressive enhancement**: Ensure graceful degradation
